I have just one suggestion for those working on caste and land relations in India: read and re-read Jotiba #Phule & Dr #Ambedkar (n/n). Additionally, read regional agrarian/social histories pertaining to different states. (n/n)

Frameworks of land acquisition and accumulation by dispossession can hardly be applied to extremely high levels of landlessness among #Dalits. And, it has limited utility to understand the contemporary caste & land structure in rural India, except in few special contexts (3/n)

Without understanding the historical relationship b/w caste and landholding, it is almost impossible to comprehend its nature and contemporary manifestation. It is very sad then to see, day in and day out, how most scholars reduce this question to "dispossession" alone (2/n)

Just came across the special issue of a major international academic journal on #caste & #land in #India. Unarguably, the caste & land question constitutes the most important challenge of our times. This question has its roots in the unique social structure of India. (1/n)
